RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 86. Maiden Special Weight Purse 80000. (UP TO $13,920 NYSBFOA) FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RESERVE CURRENCY five then four wide in pursuit down the backstretch, tucked three wide near the half mile pole before tucking to the two path into the turn, raced very briefly inside midway before tipping out once more placed to coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung four wide into upper stretch and overhauled the front taking command at the quarter pole, went clear under a drive to prevail. SYSTEMIC CHANGE coaxed from the gate, chased four then three wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun two to three wide for home, ran on to chase the winner home clear of the rest and along second best. PREDICTED chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, swung six wide into upper stretch, improved position to secure the show honors. CORTON CHARLEMAGNE chased two to three wide until tucked inside through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, went eight wide into upper stretch and weakened. MISTICAL CURLIN hustled from the gate, chased along the inside under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, took the inside route into upper stretch and tired. VODKA MARDINI coaxed from the start, showed the way early on from the two path knocking heads with a rival, got displaced from command and came under coaxing near the half mile pole, continued just off the inside through the turn and into upper stretch pushed along, lost action in his hind legs while folding and was eased home across the finish.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR ATTITUDE settled off the pace, moved closer outside the half-mile pole, ranged up in the four path around the turn, took the advantage outside the quarter-pole, remained on his inside lead while battling with the runner-up until inside the furlong marker, swapped to the proper lead at that juncture then edged clear under strong urging. STEADY PROGRESS brushed with a foe early, showed speed between horses, dropped back with six furlongs to run then tracked the pace, made a bid in the three path on the turn, turned into the stretch under the crop, fought with the winner into the final furlong then was outfinished while clear for the place. HOME SCHOOL settled off the pace, was urged along late on the backstretch, saved ground for most of the turn then shifted three wide, came six wide into the stretch and improved for the show. SECOND AND REED disputed the pace on the inside of foes, vied along the rail under urging early on the turn, dropped back with three furlongs to run, came off the rail late on that bend, moved out into upper stretch and weakened. SARATOGA STRONG brushed with an opponent early, showed speed on the outside, moved in inside the three-quarter pole, contested the pace outside of a rival, vied in the two path on the turn, moved to the rail while dropping back late on that bend and tired. PRACTICALLYMINE dropped back at the start, settled under some urging, was urged along in the three path around the turn, spun five wide into the stretch and failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRINK THE WIND bumped with a rival at the start, disputed the pace on the outside, vied in the three to four path early on the turn, dropped to the two path while moving clear later on that bend, responded well under a strong hand-ride in upper stretch, was given one pop of a right-handed crop coming to the furlong marker then switched to a left-handed crop and held under strong urging. BIG VENEZUELA settled off the pace, moved out with about six furlongs to run, moved closer while urged four wide around the turn, chased the winner in the stretch, gained on that foe to the wire but missed while well clear for the place. LORD GATLING settled off the pace, was given his cue in the two path on the turn, came four wide into the stretch under a drive and just earned the show while no match for the top two. NORGAY bumped with a rival at the start then was hustled, raced outside under urging, went three wide on the turn, was driven five wide into the stretch and came up empty. BUCKINGHAM PRINCE was fractious in the gate then backed out and deemed fit to run by the state veterinarian, showed good speed, disputed the pace on the inside of the winner, dropped back in the two path midway through the turn and faded. CLASH A. J. was fractious in the gate, raced at the rear under urging, saved ground on the turn and was no factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TREASURE TROVE just off the inside through the first turn, chased three then two wide from near the rear of the field, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, rallied to issue a challenge to his barn and stable mate through the final furlong knocking heads until taking command seventy yards from home, then inched away to the finish to prevail. WAR STOPPER chased along the inside under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, angled three wide into upper stretch, weakened in the drive.
